title: Pauline Hanson On What The Liberal Leadership Spill Could Mean For One Nation | 10 News+
description: Sussan Ley's resignation from Parliament means a by-election is coming in her vast regional seat in southern New South Wales. title: Trump Says Iran Regime Change Would Be The ‘Best Thing’ As US Military Prepares Options | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump says a change in power in Iran “would be the best thing that could happen”, as his administration weighs potential military action against Tehran.  Trump confirmed a second aircraft carrier, the USS Gerald R. Ford, is being deployed to the Middle East, joining the USS Abraham Lincoln.  He says the build-up is needed “in case we don’t make a deal”, as indirect nuclear talks with Iran remain uncertain.  Regional allies warn any strike could ignite a broader Middle East conflict, as nuclear negotiations stall and internal unrest intensifies pressure on Tehran’s leadership. title: Angus Taylor Ousts Sussan Ley, Sets Sights On Property Tax Fight | 10 News
description: Newly elected Liberal leader Angus Taylor and his deputy Jane Hume have hit the ground running, a day after deposing Sussan Ley in a party room coup.
